Project Reflection:

After completing this assignment, I have a new perspective on my online identity.
I used to think of social media as strictly a personal platform.
When I created accounts on LinkedIn and GitHub as well as created a profile on ResearchGate, I began to think about how important it is to establish your "personal brand" in your career early on.
One of the biggest difficulties I had was trying to summarize my goals in one line for my GitHub README file, which made me reflect on what I want my branch to look like in the next few years.
Before I created my ResearchGate profile, I didn't think about the academic side of what I am doing in my branch. Now that I have created this profile, I see how it provides a line of communication between myself and academics in my field. 
I now realize that simply having these profiles is not enough.
The value of these accounts will come from having continual updates to my GitHub with snippets of code, reading research papers, and networking through LinkedIn while going through my educational experience.
